thus far reacted 21 points; United States Steel,\n9 points; Westinghouse, S; Anaconda, 19; American Can,\n19; Consolidated Gas, 5; Bethlehem Steel, 19; New York\nCentral Railroad, IS; and Chrysler Motor, 5 points. The\namusement stocks and the utilities, with a few Os the\nspecialties, are still able to \u201ccarry on,\u201d and rive no appear\nance of having reached the end of their rope for the\ntime being.\nWhether the reaction described above has accomplished\nthe \"correction\" of the market\u2019s technical position remains\nto be seen. The reneral impression in Wall Street is that\nthe market has rone as far as it can in discounting easy\nmoney conditions and that its immediate future course is\ndistinctly \u201cup to\u201d the business revival. Frankly this has\nbeen a disappointment in many lines, which have required\nmore time than was popularly allotted to recover from the\ncrash of late 1929.\nIf the current year is to compare favorably with last\nyear and the year before that, the \u201cHr three\u201d fa industry\n(steel, buildinr construction and automobile manufacturing)\nmust shortly quicken their stride; car loadings must in\ncrease and the ranks of the employed materially swell.\nMeanwhile, a 992,909,999 increase in brokers* loans indicates\na further distribution of stocks.\nConsolidated Oas\nTh< impressive action of this\ninvestment favorite in yesterday\u2019s\nreactionary session seems to indi\ncate that some deal of import\nance is hanging fire which\nshould favorably affect the stock.\nThe large block of more than\n100,000 sharbs of this issue which\nwas purchased by United Corpora\ntion is further evidence of the\nconstant shrinking floating sup\nply which has made Consolidated\nGas so responsive to buying de\nmand. In comparison with the\nsharp upturn in other less sea\nsoned utility issues, the market\npossibilities of this stock still ap\npear favorable.\nAir Reduction\nThe first quarterly report of\nthis chemical issue makes pleas\nant reading for the market fol\nlowers who has been beset by a\nlong list of discouraging state\nments which have thus far come\nto hand. For the first three\nmonths of the year net earnings\nof 91,523,278, or 94 94 per share\ncompare with 91.237,562 or 91-87\nin the like period of last year.\nThe vast strides that this com-\nLOCAL PRODUCE\nButter \u2014One-pound prints, 41c; tube,\n42c. Eggs\u2014Hennery, 27024 c; current\nreceipts, lifts.\nLive Poultry\u2014Turkeys, young, 150\n3Sc; old, 22025 c; spring broilers, 41c;\nwinter chickens, 15c; leghorns, 13035 c;\ncapons, 25038 c; ducks, 15O10c; hens,\n280 25c; roosters, 18c; keats, 80 0 85c.\nDressed turkeys, young', 32015 c; old,\n28c; spring broilers, 40045 c. Winter\nchickens, 35 0 38c; leghorns, 35c; fowls,\n30<32c; capons, 40045 c. Ducks, 250\n28c; keats, 80050 c.\nMeats, Fresh Killed\u2014Beef, 20023 c;\nveal, 28 030 c; iambs, 33c; pork loins, 28\nO30c; fresh haras, ?4c; fresh shoulders,\n22c; smoked hams. 28c; lard in pack\nages, llftc; in bulk. 13c; smoked shoul\nders, 20023 c; bacon, 28c.\nUv\u00ab Stock \u2014Calves, lie; lambs, 100\n12c; spring lambs, 13014 c.\nApples\u2014Supplies light, demand light,\nmarket steady. Barrels. Virginia. Wine\nsaps, U 8. No. 1,2 ft inches up. mostly\n18; unclassified. 2ft inches up, Ben\nDavis, 54.75. Boxes; Washington, Wine\nsaps, extra fancy, medium to large\nsise, 8303.25, mostly 83-25. Bushel\nbaskets: Winesaps, U. 8. No. 1,3 ft\ninches up, 82.5002.75.\nAsparagus\u2014Supplies moderate. De\nmand moderate; market steady. South\nCarolina, dqzen-bunch crates. green,\nvery large slxe, 8404.50; few fine qua.-\nitv higher; large sise, 8303.50; medium\nsixe, 3202.50; muall sise, 31.5002.\nCabbage\u2014Supplies libera!. Demand\nlight; market steady. Mouth Carolina,\nl< a -bushel hampers. Wakefields, bent,\nmostly 31.50; few high as 35.75; ordi\nnary condition. 31.\nCelery\u2014Supplies light. Demand mod\nerate; market firm. Florida. 10-ineh\ncrates, individually washed and pre\ntool